          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " The ratio of the 3-Li-6(n,alpha) to 5-B-10(n,alpha)",
                " cross-sections from 10 eV to 80 keV and recommended",
                " values of the 5-B-10(n,alpha) cross-section"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "LINAC"
                ],
                "institute": "2UK HAR"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "    45 MeV Harwell Linear Accelerator",
                "  time-of-flight spectrometer."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "PHOTO"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "    Neutron pulse width (unmoderated) = 220 ns."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The B(n,alpha) cross-section has been written in terms",
                " of an analytical expression, the form of which has",
                " been derived from theoretical arguments. This",
                " expression has been fitted to all the cross-section",
                " data and the result is given by equation. It was",
                " concluded that equation  describes the 10B(n,alpha)",
                " cross-section up to 200 keV within an accuracy ranging",
                " from 1% up to 1 keV, 2% at 10 keV, 3% at 100 keV and",
                " 5% at 200 keV and it is recommended that this equation",
                " be used where neutron fluxes are determined with",
                " detectors based on the 10B(n,alpha) reaction."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 10B sample had a total mass of 3.38 g and was",
                "7.6 cm in diameter."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "A"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  Alphas"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " The numbers given in the quantity column are",
                " ratios of average cross sections, averaged",
                " over an energy range (E - E+0.15*E). The value",
                " in the energy column represents the average energy of",
                " the range, i.e. (E+0.075*E).",
                ".Two measurements covering the ranges 10 eV- 2 keV",
                " and 50 eV- 80 keV respectively have been performed."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FLAG": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                1.0
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  The results are affected by the resonances in",
                " the detector structural materials."
              ]
            }
          ],
